<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author(s). (Year, Month Day of publication). <em>Title of web page/ article</em>. 
	Name of News website. URL
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author(s)">Youssef&#45;Shalala, A</span>. 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year, Month Day of publication)">2019, October 7</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of web page/ article">Studying for exams? Here&#8217;s how to make your memory work for you</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name of News website">The Conversation</span>. 
	<span class="hover fake-aref" title="URL">https://theconversation.com/studying-for-exams-heres-how-to-make-your-memory-work-for-you-124586</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
The URL is presented as a hyperlink.
<br>
<br>
